Abbas Tritemius, in his third Queſtion to St. Maximus Emilianus, which is ſpoken of before, ſaith thus: The devils, amongſt unfaithful people, do ſeem to raiſe up the dead to life, and to ſhew miracles to curious men, that they might as it were ſwallow them up with error in ſtead of miracles;
The devils cannot really raiſe the dead. 
and are altogether pertinacious and obſtinate: but they cannot truly and really raiſe up the dead, but do variouſly deceive the ſenſes of men, ſhewing them feigned reſemblances of the dead. For it is certainly manifeſt, that the devils can do all things, but only in a falſe ſimilitude of holy miracles in truth.
